Dent-Phelps R-III School District
July 22 at 9:45 AM ·

The Dent-Phelps administration will be meeting with the Dent County Health Department August 5th to assess the most current situation.

The re-opening plan will be will be distributed during Open House and administration will be available to answer any questions.

Open House is August 21st. 3:00-4:30 for students who’s last names begin with A-L; 5:00-6:30 for M-Z.
If you have scheduling conflicts with assigned times, please call the school and talk with an administrator to work out a different time.

School will start August 24th, and the staff at DP-R3 is working hard to ensure all students get a proper education while reducing the spread of COVID-19 and still have a somewhat normal school day.

We have been notified of a concern from the Salem R-80 school district, and want to share the following message with the families of our middle school students who are planning to attend athletic camps at Salem R-80.

Message from Salem R-80:
We have someone associated with the sports program being tested for COVID today. This person does not know of any exposure, but is using an abundance of caution and being tested due to some symptoms. As soon as testing results are in we will be in contact to let you know necessary recommendations, if any. Again, we do not have any evidence this person came in contact with someone with COVID. We are simply trying to be proactive and transparent so you can make an educated decision as parents, regarding your child's participation in this week's athletic events.

post_text:
At the June board meeting the school board recognized Mr. Ron Copeland and Mr. Kevin Creighton.
Mr. Copeland served the Dent-Phelps R-3 community for 9 years on the school board. Ron decided not to run again for school board to pursue another public office.
Mr. Creighton served as the school principal for 4 years and decided to further his career in a larger district.
Presenting the board’s appreciation is the board President, Will Loughridge and Vice President, Frank Barnitz. We wish both Ron and Kevin well in their future endeavors.
At the board meeting, Nick Gover and Caleb Gidcumb took the oath of office to serve as the district’s new board members. Welcome aboard!

At the board meeting, Nick Gover and Caleb Gidcumb took the oath of office to serve as the district’s new board members. Welcome aboard!

post_text:
The Dent-Phelps R-III School Board would like to thank all of the district’s resident’s and staff that attended last night’s public meeting. The meeting was to discuss the school applying for a Start Date Exemption to start the 20-21 school year early. The school board appreciated and listened to all of the comments and concerns presented. The school board then decided not to take the next step in applying to the state for the exemption.
School will begin August 24, 2020 as originally planned and will follow the calendar that was adopted by the board in February.
The school board and the staff are diligently working on ways to recover from the spring shut-down, and open school as safely as possible for the students. More information on these plans will be forthcoming.
This will take all of us – students, parents, staff, and school board working together, but our community is strong and the Dent-Phelps family will continue to move forward.

Public Notice
Notice of Public Meeting
Dent-Phelps R-III School – Cafeteria or Gymnasium
June 16, 2020 6:30 pm.

The Dent-Phelps R-III School Board will be holding a public meeting June 16, 2020 at 6:30 pm. to discuss starting the 2020-2021 school year earlier than August 24, 2020. The State Board of Education is authorized to grant an exemption to the state law on the start date of school for 2020-2021 only due to the COVID-19 pandemic. The Dent-Phelps R-III School Board is considering the option and would like the input of the district’s residents. The meeting will be held at the school in the cafeteria or gymnasium.

Dent-Phelps R-III School District
May 22 at 11:13 AM ·

Attention 8th Grade Parents and Community Members!

The Dent-Phelps R-III School Board has officially set the date for 8th Grade Graduation this year. We are planning on holding our Graduation Ceremony on July 16th at 7:00pm in the school gymnasium.

We will be incorporating Student Awards into the graduation ceremony, and as such we will not be hosting the awards banquet this year.

We know that this is not how we wanted to end our year, but we hope that by holding this ceremony we can still take the time to honor our graduating Dent-Phelps Bobcats, and give them a proper send off as they move onto High School next year!

More information related to the logistics of how the ceremony will operate will be provided as we approach the date in July.

School will be open from 8:00am - 8:00pm Monday through Wednesday this week for parents to turn in students completed work and pick up student items that were left at school. All work must be turned in by 8:00pm Wednesday in order to be graded.

As a reminder, our food service program will end on Friday, May 15th.

Grade cards for all students will be mailed home next week.

Thank you everyone for all that you are doing for our students, and happy LAST WEEK OF SCHOOL!

Attention Middle School / High School Parents! Those interested in fall sports with Salem R-80, please note the following updates about sports in the fall:

7th and 8th Grade Fall Middle school Co-Op sports (Cross Country for Girls/Boys and Football) - Student middle school practices will start on August 17th this year. Please note that this is BEFORE the first days of school.

9th-12th grade Athletes - Fall varsity sports start on August 10th. This will include cross county, football, and girls softball.

It is important if you plan to play any sport in Salem in the fall that you are present on the first day of practice! If you have any questions, please contact Coach Karr at the high-school of Coach Lindsey at Dent-Phelps.

Thank you!

Parents! Our second wave of Continued Learning Activities are available for pickup at the school daily from 9:00am until 2:00pm. Additionally, we have library books available for anyone who is running low, and we have various supplies ready for anyone who needs them!

Don't forget, we will have the option to turn in work available each Monday from 9:00am until 2:00pm. There will be a work box set out in the Foyer next to the available supplies. Work will be distributed to the teachers to grade the following week. If you cannot turn in work online, or make the scheduled turn in time on Monday, please contact your classroom teacher to make other arrangements.

Thank you to everyone for all of the work you are doing to keep our students engaged in learning!

post_text:
IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT: Parents and community members, due to the ongoing situation with the COVID-19 Virus and out of an abundance of caution, Dent-Phelps R-III has decided to extend our scheduled school closure through April 24th, with the first day back planned as being April 27th. All scheduled school activities will also be canceled through this time frame.

After considering the extension of the national recommendations for social distancing, and after carefully consulting with local health officials, it has been determined that the safest decision for our students, families, and staff would be to extend our school closure. We will continue to evaluate the situation and consult with local health officials on if this closure should be extended beyond this time frame. We will continue to communicate with our families and communities as soon as we have more information.

More information on this closure and our plans for continued learning will be made available this evening through our schools Facebook and our mass notification system.

post_text:
CHALLENGE TIME! Our upper grade students did this challenge yesterday, so today it is our Elementary Students turn!

Challenge: Clean, disinfect, and count every door knob in your house. Then, depending on your grade level, post the answer to the question below:

Kindergarten: how many door knobs did you clean?
1st and 2nd Grade: How many door knobs did you clean? Take that number and add 12 to that number. Now add 17 more.

3rd and 4th Grade - Take the number of door knobs and multiple by 4. Now multiply that answer by 5.

Post your answers below!

Hey Dent-Phelps Families! How are you doing on establishing a daily learning routine for your child? Check out Mr. Creighton's daily routine if you want some ideas, and feel free to post some of your own routine ideas in the comments.

Having a daily routine established early is the best way to keep your child in a learning mindset! We encourage all families to start with their routines early and, if possible, keep with those routines through the next two weeks so that your child comes back to school fresh and ready with the skills they need for success!

As a result of the ongoing situation with the COVID-19 virus, Dent-Phelps R-III will be closed beginning Wednesday, March 18th through Friday, April 3rd. Classes will resume on Monday, April 6th.

More information will be made available this evening both on Facebook and through our Bright Arrow notification system.

The COVID-19 pandemic is presenting a unique challenge to our world community, and we have been working diligently to coordinate our efforts with local health officials, state level officials, and the Centers for Disease Control.

We will also be communicating more information tomorrow related to opportunities for our students to engage in continued learning through this break. If you have not already, please like and share our schools Facebook page in order to stay up to date on ongoing information.

Kevin Creighton
Principal
Dent-Phelps R-III

post_text:
It is with a heavy heart that we announce today that Mr. Kevin Creighton will be leaving the Dent-Phelps R-III school district at the conclusion of this school year. Although he will be missed, we are excited for him to take the next steps in his career as he assumes the head Principal position at McCulloch elementary school in Republic Missouri next year.

Mr. Creighton has been a part of the Dent-Phelps R-III family for the last seven years, serving three years as our middle school science teacher and the last four years as our school principal.

The school board, district administration, and the district leadership team will be beginning the search for our next building leader. Mr. Creighton will continue to serve Dent-Phelps R-III as principal for the remainder of this school year, after which he and his family will be relocating to Republic.

post_text:
For those who missed the note that was sent home, we are happy to announce that our Local School Board has authorized improvements for our gym! Within the coming months, the gym will see new heating and air conditioning installed and new bleachers. These projects have been talked about for a while and will be a tremendous improvement on the gym.

The first project will be the bleachers, which will be installed over Christmas break. This project will require us to tear out the old bleachers in preparation for the instillation of the new ones. This will mean that the annual Christmas program for Kindergarten through Fourth grade will be rescheduled as a Winter Recital that will take place January 16th at 6:00pm so that everyone can see and enjoy the new bleachers.

post_text:
We would like to say a big Thank You to Intercounty Electric for their support of the Dent-Phelps R-III Space Camp trip over the past several years!

With their help and generous donations, we have been able to send over 112 Dent County students to the US Space and Rocket Center in Huntsville, Alabama.

Our students have learned about the history of the space program, manned Mission Control during a "Shuttle Mission," built their own rockets, and experienced possible careers involving Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math! Thank you for helping to make a difference in the lives of our students.

Our staff member spotlight for this week is Mrs. Heithold! Mrs. Heithold started teaching at Dent-Phelps R-III in 2006, and has taught Kindergarten for the last 14 years.

Mrs. Heithold graduated with a bachelors degree in Early Childhood Education from the Missouri State University (formerly SMSU) in 2004, then immediately started work on a graduate degree. In May 2007 she received a Masters Degree in Education from Southwest Baptist University.

Mrs. Heithold has been married to her husband Chad for 12 years, and they have three healthy, smart, and active children: James, Adam, and Grace.

She loves to read, create learning activities for her students, and visit National and State parks with her family.

Our staff member spotlight for this week highlights Ms. Atkinson! She holds a Bachelor's degree in Elementary Education and a certification in Early Childhood education. Ms. Atkinson has been teaching since 2011, and came to Dent-Phelps R-III in 2013. She currently teaches 5th and 6th grade science, and is a member of our schools Leadership Team and our Staff Motivators Team.

Outside of school, Ms. Atkinson loves the St. Louis Cardinals, being outdoors, baking, and pinterest. She also participates in the Hero's Half Marathon every year! She also has two children: Mallory and Joseph.

In her classroom you can find a large variety of hands on activities that help students to better understand the concepts being taught, a positive and fun learning environment, and various other activities to help students better grasp the concepts being taught. post_text:
Our Staff member spotlight for this week features our Superintendent, Mrs. Victoria Brooker!

Mrs. Brooker is currently in her ninth year as superintendent for Dent-Phelps R-III. Prior to that she served four years as building Principal and in a dual Principal/Superintendent role. She started her time at Dent-Phelps R-III as a Library Media Specialist and 5th Grade Classroom teacher.

Mrs. Brooker was born in Georgia and was raised on Army bases around the world. She served this nation for seven years in the United States Army as a Military Police Officer.

At home, she enjoys reading and building Jigsaw puzzles. She also loves to spend time with her husband, help kids, and play with animals (especially her dogs!).

Mrs. Brooker holds a Bachelor of Science in Education Degree that she received from Drury University. She also has a Masters of Science in Education from Southwest Baptist University, where she also has her Specialist in Superintendency as well.

post_text:
For our second staff member spotlight, this week we bring you Mrs. LeAnn Shults! Mrs. Shults is in her second year at Dent-Phelps as the School Secretary.

Mrs. Shults has been doing clerical related jobs for the past 34 years. Prior to being at Dent-Phelps she was employed at Selam R-80 for nine years. She is a graduate from Salem High School in 1986, and attended college at SBU in Salem.

In her spare time, she loves spending time with her wonderful husband, Rick, to whom she has been married for over 30 years. She has one precious daughter, Rachel, and they love spending time together as a family and with their fur babies: Cheeks, London, and Cussie. Her hobbies include cooking and reading.

She is a proud member of our Dent-Phelps R-III family!

post_text:
This week will start our first ever Staff Member Spotlight! This is a way for us to highlight the amazing staff we have at our school, and help you get to know the great people your children will interact with every day.

Our first staff member spotlight will start with Mr. Creighton. He currently serves as the Principal of Dent-Phelps R-3 and is in his 4th year in that role. Prior to that he served as the Middle School Science teacher, also at Dent Phelps.

Outside of school Mr Creighton enjoys the outdoors, spending time with his family, training and competing in the sport of StrongMan, and Volunteering with the Missouri Boys State Program and his local church.

Mr Creighton was born and raised near Rolla Missouri, completed his Undergraduate degree in Science Education at Missouri S&T, and completed his Masters In Administration at Southwest Baptist University.

Reminder: Open House is tonight from 6:00pm-8:00pm. New students will be able to enroll, and all families will have an opportunity to meet their teachers. Doors will open to the gym at 5:30pm so parents can meet bus drivers, and doors will open for parents to go to classrooms at 6:00pm. We hope to see everyone there!

Note: There are significant changes to bus routes this year, so all parents must go to the gym before going to meet their teachers.
